<br>
<DIV class="poemtitle">Travelling Exhibition</DIV><br>
  <div align="center"><img src="images/travelingexhibition.jpg"><br>
  <a class="artistline" href="javascript:goauthor('jones');">art by Pat Jones</a></div><br>
<TABLE><TR><TD>
<br>
<br>
Room by room they packed up the museum.<br />
  They filled up armored suits with porcelain,<br />
  The urns with lesser urns. They wrapped the busts<br />
  In   bubble paper, squeezing now and then<br />
  Mini-explosions, just for fun, like   Queen<br />
  Victoria's little wars. The paintings posed<br />
  A problem. Smaller ones in plastic sacks,<br />
  That would just do; but 19th-century<br />
  Gigantists&#8212;lacking room enough and twine,<br />
  Necessity made them inverts, hauled them out,<br />
  Hoping for fair and fine. It took a   while.<br />
  The Judgement of Solomon, a red and gold<br />
  Simeon Smythe, took 12 old  men to tote,<br />
  Curators with post-docs and 3 rosettes<br />
  Amongst them. When they propped the painting back<br />
  Against the mini-van to rest, it glowed.<br />
  A minion in the right foreground held out<br />
  A scimitar, prepared to bisect babes<br />
  On the command. One of the old men said,<br />
  Where is a  minion where you really need one?<br />
  They left a head of Nero on the roof.<br />
  It sneered and skittered as they took the turn.<br />
<br>
<br><br>
<A href="page5.htm?5#" onClick="goauthor('epstein');return false">by Richard Epstein</a><br><br><br>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
